<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="1079" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1079">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3674.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">
                                <persName type="from">Manuel L. Luján</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-20">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 20, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>As delegate from General Pascual Orozco, commander in chief of the
                            Mexican revolutionary army, I beg to convey to you the respects of
                            General Orozco. Should the United States Government see fit to honor
                            General Orozco with any communication I, as his representative, with
                            full powers, am instructed to receive such communication and to make
                            known to you my place of residence in this country. I shall be honored
                            to present to your excellency my personal respects and credentials
                            whenever your Government feels so disposed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Manuel L. Luján</hi></signed>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">225 West 80th St., New York City, N. Y.</hi>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>